position ml engineer items team. company httpstabbyaien-ae. location eu remote we cannot hire in russia but could assist with relocation to georgia armenia portugal spain serbia about tabby. tabby creates financial freedom in the way people shop earn and save by reshaping their relationship with money. the companys flagship offering allows shoppers to split their payments online and in-store with no interest or fees over 32000 global brands and small businesses including amazon noon ikea and shein use tabby to accelerate growth and gain loyal customers by offering easy and flexible payments online and in stores. tabby has generated over 7 billion in transaction volume for its partner brands and has the highest rated most reviewed largest and fastest growing app of any fintech in the gcc region. tabby launched operations in 2020 and has raised +1 billion in equity and debt funding from global and regional investors the opportunity. we are hiring a ml engineer to join our items team who will help us implement the mechanics of processing items in the marketplace key responsibilities. - development of algorithms for items matching and items moderation. - development of algorithms for parsing and enriching product information. - deployment and integrating ml models as services. - bringing best practices of working with mlops infrastructure essential qualifications. - 3+ years of experience as an ml engineer or data scientist. - experience and achievements in the ml domain within e-commerce. - good knowledge of python understanding of best practices. - basic knowledge of sql. - experience of extracting information from unstructured data. - familiarity with text andor image transformers bonus skills. - experience working with nosql vectors databases ann indexes. - self-hosting of llms. - developing streaming and batch data processing pipelines. - model deployment experience airflow docker. - experience on google cloud platform what you can expect. - we offer flexible working hours and trust you to work enough hours to do your job well at times that suit you and your team. - a working environment that gives you autonomy and responsibility from day one. - you should be comfortable with the idea that the quality of your work will influence the shape of your career. - participation in companys employee stock options program. - health insurance. - we are passionate about creating an inclusive high-performing workplace that gives people from all backgrounds the support they need to thrive grow and meet their goals whatever they may be. - if this sounds exciting to you wed love to hear from you how to apply. if you would like to join tabby and feel that position matches your experience please submit your resume for this role at httpsboardsgreenhouseioforgoodaijobs4173028007
